# Price Data Pipeline

## Data Provider: TwelveData
- Primary provider is TwelveData (`DATA_PROVIDER=twelvedata`). Use TwelveData wherever possible: price feed, quotes, historical bars, backfill. Alpaca is used for execution and as fallback when TwelveData is unavailable.
- `parseTdQuote()` in `worker/twelvedata.js` MUST parse all native fields from `/quote?prepost=true`: `change`, `percent_change`, `extended_change`, `extended_percent_change`, `extended_price`, `is_market_open`.
- Price feed cron jobs MUST prefer TwelveData's native change fields over manual `price - prevClose` computation.

## KV Price Format (`timed:prices`)
- Short keys: `p` (price), `pc` (prev close), `dc` (day change $), `dp` (day change %), `dh`/`dl`/`dv` (daily high/low/volume), `t` (timestamp).
- Extended hours: `ahp` (extended price), `ahdc` (AH change $), `ahdp` (AH change %).
- **Value timestamps are mandatory**: `q_ts` (vendor quote/event receipt) and `p_ts` (last actual price move). ALL freshness gates (`isPriceValueFresh`, client `quoteReceiptTs`) key off these — never poll `t`. EVERY writer (cron REST, stale sweep, WS stream DO) MUST stamp them and never regress an existing stamp (`mergeStreamRowIntoKv`). A writer that omits them makes its own prices invisible: gates reject the rows and the UI serves the prior-day scoring close (MU/WDC/SOXL 2026-07-07).
- Blob-level fields (`stale_symbols`, `stale_symbol_count`, `market_open`) must survive partial writers — the stream DO preserves them on rewrite.
- Display-staleness guardrail: `price_value_freshness` cron op pages when ≥10 symbols have value stamps >20 min old during RTH; `/timed/health` exposes writer-independent `valueStaleCount`/`valueStaleSymbols`.
- Session-aware persistence using `isNyRegularMarketOpen()` (handles holidays, weekends, early closes):
  - **Market closed**: Preserve previous `dc`/`dp`/`pc` when TwelveData zeros them out (day-roll). Preserve `ahp`/`ahdc`/`ahdp` so EXT movers row stays visible.
  - **Market open (RTH)**: Let fresh values flow through. NEVER write `ahp`/`ahdc`/`ahdp` to KV during RTH — TwelveData returns stale extended-hours values even when the market is open. Gate on `isNyRegularMarketOpen()` before populating ext fields. Frontend also guards: cards/movers suppress EXT display when `isNyRegularMarketOpen()` is true.

## Frontend: Single Source of Truth
- `getDailyChange(t)` in `react-app/shared-price-utils.js` is the ONLY way to compute daily change. Returns `{ dayPct, dayChg }`.
- `getHeadlinePrice(t)` is session-aware: RTH uses `_live_price`; outside RTH uses today's RTH close (`close`/`price`), never stale extended prints on the headline line.
- Every page showing daily change MUST import `shared-price-utils.js` and use `getDailyChange()`. NEVER use raw `t.dailyChgPct` or inline computation.
- Server endpoints returning ticker data MUST include field aliases (`prev_close`, `day_change_pct`, `day_change`) so getDailyChange's fallback chain works.
- Applies to: Cards (index-react.html), Right Rail, Open Trades Table (trades page), Investor Dashboard, Top Movers bar.
- **Outside RTH client merge**: `timed:prices` field `p` is the RTH close; extended print is `ahp`. Frontend polls (`tt-live-data.js`, index-react) MUST still write `price`, `close`, and `_live_price` when the market is closed. Do not skip the merge thinking `p` is an extended tick.
- **`/timed/all` micro_cache**: the 5-min fast path MUST run `overlayTimedPricesRow` before returning — it bypasses the full assembly path that normally overlays live prices.
- **`overlayTimedPricesRow`**: when `!marketOpen`, set `obj.close = pfP` so `getHeadlinePrice` does not read a stale `close == prev_close` scoring snapshot.

## RTH/ETH Movers
- Top Gainers/Losers has two rows: RTH (intraday, `getDailyChange(t).dayPct`) and EXT (extended hours, `_ah_change_pct`).
- **Market open**: EXT row auto-hides (AH fields cleared during RTH).
- **Market closed**: EXT row shows last-known data, persists overnight/weekends/holidays.
- Crypto tickers (BTCUSD, ETHUSD) are excluded from the EXT row (24/7 markets, no session distinction).

## Entitlement Gating & Attribution
- Live price/change data **and** proprietary scores/SL/TP go to **Pro, VIP, and Admin only**. Server-side: `canAccessLivePrices()` in `worker/api.js` (tier ∈ {`pro`, `admin`}; `computeUserDataTier` collapses VIP → `pro`) + `redactTickerMapForTier()`. Frontend display gate: `window._ttIsPro` (= Pro/VIP/Admin).
- **Members** (signed in, never passed the Stripe paywall → code tier `free`) and **anonymous** visitors get NEITHER prices nor scores (snapshot fields stripped; `/timed/prices` + `/timed/ws-ticket` return a structured empty/403). There is no real "free" user — the code's `free` tier == a Member.
- Footer MUST include "Market data powered by Twelve Data" for licensing compliance.
